breakpoint.description:
The breakpoint value. The default is `{{width}}px`.

**Note**: This breakpoint value is not supported in CSS media queries.

**Example**:
```css
/* Modify the breakpoint value */
:root {
  {{name}}: {{newWidth}}px;
}
```

darkLightTheme.description:
**{{colorName}}**

RGB color value for {{modeName}}, separated by commas.

By modifying this property, you can change the color value under {{modeName}}.

**Example**:
```css
/* Set {{modeName}} color value */
:root {
  {{name}}: 255, 0, 0;
}

/* Read {{modeName}} color value */
.element {
  color: rgb(var({{name}}));
}

/* Read the color value that automatically adapts */
.element {
  color: rgb(var({{nameAuto}}));
}

/* Read the color value that automatically adapts and add opacity */
.element {
  color: rgba(var({{nameAuto}}), 0.5);
}
```

autoTheme.description:
**{{colorName}}**

RGB color value that automatically adapts to light and dark modes, separated by commas.

To set this color value, it is recommended to set `{{nameLight}}` and `{{nameDark}}` separately.

**Example**:
```css
/* Read the color value that automatically adapts */
.element {
  color: rgb(var({{name}}));
}

/* Read the color value that automatically adapts and add opacity */
.element {
  color: rgba(var({{name}}), 0.5);
}

/* Set the color values for light mode and dark mode separately */
:root {
  {{nameLight}}: 255, 0, 0;
  {{nameDark}}: 255, 0, 0;
}
```

elevation.description:
Shadow value for elevation level {{value}}.

**Example**:
```css
/* Set the shadow value for elevation level {{value}} */
:root {
  {{name}}: 0 0.5px 1.5px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.19);
}

/* Read the shadow value for elevation level {{value}} */
.element {
  box-shadow: var({{name}});
}
```

easing.description:
Easing curve for {{easingName}}.

**Example**:
```css
/* Set the easing curve for {{easingName}} */
:root {
  {{name}}: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
}

/* Read the easing curve for {{easingName}} */
.element {
  transition-timing-function: var({{name}});
}
```

duration.description:
Animation duration for {{value}}{{level}}.

**Example**:
```css
/* Set the animation duration for {{value}}{{level}} */
:root {
  {{name}}: 0.3s;
}

/* Read the animation duration for {{value}}{{level}} */
.element {
  transition-duration: var({{name}});
}
```

corner.description:
Corner radius value for level {{value}}.

**Example**:
```css
/* Set the corner radius value for level {{value}} */
:root {
  {{name}}: 4px;
}

/* Read the corner radius value for level {{value}} */
.element {
  border-radius: var({{name}});
}
```

stateLayer.description:
Opacity of the state layer for the `{{state}}` state.

**Example**:
```css
/* Set the opacity of the state layer for the {{state}} state */
:root {
  {{name}}: 0.1;
}
```
